<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-06-26T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-06-26T12:00:00-05:00" n="60" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d60">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">811.248/607: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Afghanistan</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Thayer</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Kabul</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-06-26T21:00:00+04:00">June 26,
                                    1942—9 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received June 26—4:58 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>19. The Legation has just been informed by New Delhi of the violation of
                            Afghan territory yesterday by an American aircraft. Because of the
                            seriousness with which the Afghan Government might view the incident and
                            because of long delay in receipt of telegrams from Department the
                            Legation without awaiting instructions is expressing regrets on behalf
                            of the American Government to the Minister of Foreign Affairs.<note n="23" xml:id="d60fn23">All Mohammed Khan.</note>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Thayer</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>